# Verify Backend App Is Running

Confirm backend app starts without runtime errors — follow sequence.

## 1. Local infra first

Postgres + Redis up before `serve`. See `docker-local-infra.mdc`:

```bash
cd backend
npm run docker:up
docker compose exec postgres pg_isready -U resharing
docker compose exec redis redis-cli ping
```

No app start if infra missing or unhealthy.

## 2. Node version

From `backend/`:

```bash
nvm use 25
```

## 3. Start the app (only this pattern)

Always **serve** via Nx — never ad-hoc `node`, `ts-node`, or direct `nest start`:

```bash
cd backend
npx nx run <appName> -t serve
```

Examples: `npx nx run location-service -t serve`, `npx nx run frontend-api -t serve`.

Background when smoke check only.

## 4. Watch logs for 10 seconds

After start, monitor stdout/stderr **10 seconds**. **Startup failure** (fix before claiming app runs):

- `ERROR [Nest` / `Nest can't` / `NestFactory`
- `ExceptionHandler` / unhandled promise rejection stack traces
- `EADDRINUSE`, `ECONNREFUSED` (DB/Redis), Prisma/migration connection errors
- Process exits or no successful listen line

**Healthy start** when:

- `Nest application successfully started`
- `Listening on` / `Application is running on`

Errors within 10s → stop serve, report log excerpt, fix root cause — no broken server left running.

## 5. Cleanup

After verification, stop background `serve` (Ctrl+C or kill shell job)
